The postmaster has received a commission from the city Records Office for a complete cartographic survey of Midgaard's districts for the Registry's updated urban ledger. The current maps are years out of date and fail to account for renovations, new passages, and changes to the civic layout since the Lantern Reforms. Walk every accessible room in the city and return when your survey is complete.
Your cartographic survey has been accepted into the Registry archive and is already being used to update the district rolls. The Records Office has forwarded a commendation to the Ledgerhouse noting that this is the most complete survey of Midgaard since the original Lantern Reform documentation. Future travelers and couriers will navigate by the routes you mapped.

